<br>
What ever I do it wont be right decision for everyone, and someone will bitch at me for it, like already here.<br>
<br>
I want handwraps and tunics for Ramel and Tasker... Its important to me that we show our monks some love... and show will will go to many lengths to help them be best they can be.<br>
<br>
However... As soon as we are capable of, With the above, at least shown a huge effort to do so... I will awaken the sleeper and this whole mess can be over with and we can move on. cause all it is doing, is stalling us.<br>
<br>
As for not suporting the Guild in our decision, Its your progitive, do it publiclly and show decesion, and there will be something done about it.<br>
<br>
We can have set days and time spawns, and try new things, and etc etc, but right now its all about Sleepers, sleepers, keys keys, Important step, yes, but we have all the loot we NEED from there with the exception of the loots we mentioned above. <br>
<br>
<br>
My response was two-fold, first I started a thread on the FaF member board describing the reasons for not waking the Sleeper and challenging anyone to name a reason to wake him.  The only reason given in the thread by the time of my de-guilding was because I didn't want it woken.  Notably and no surprise Bako did not reply to the thread.<br>
<br>
Second I sent an email to Xarpolis asking about his guild because 9 months has let me know that Bako would likely wake the Sleeper, even if he couldn't counter my arguments for not waking it and I would immediately de-guild over waking Sleeper because of the action and more importantly the attitude it represents to the game.<br>
<br>
I did what I could to prevent the waking of the Sleeper and the player led destruction of the fun a zone offers, but I've done all I could and it could easily not be enough.<br>
<br>
It's time for the community at large to take up the cause, hey Syni, Bako would deprive you warders because he cares more about slowing down Resolution than your fun, would you like to fight them?  Let him know if you do.<br>
<br>
Bako's post is so contrary to fun in the game, regardless of rumors what I play for, that I copied it and have had it saved as a Word Pad document since it was posted, I was well aware it could come to this point.<br>
<br>
If mods want to delete this because the source of the quote is a private forum, feel free, but shoulder some blame if the Sleeper is awakened.<br>
<br>
BTW Bako, un-ban me from the board and give me access to the raid forum or another unused forum or I'll say my goodbyes on the FV Board.  9 months and I have some things to say to some people and to the guild as a whole, your choice where I post those thoughts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uheagan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Heagan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>One Feisty Dwarf!</span><br>  Posts: 544<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/23/02 5:54:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hihi</span><hr size=1> I would think about joining AS myself if they'd get rid of the bought characters and players who buy them.<br>
