<br>
1) Name in lights.  Only one guild ever on a server gets to do it.  Depending on who you talk to, it's a mark of Fame, or a mark of Infamy.<br>
<br>
2) Blocking off other guilds.  The warders drop primal weapons (<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> really</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> nice) and some other really nice items.  If you awaken the sleeper (by slaying all 4 warders), the warders never respawn ever again.  Primal weapons can still be gotten, but it's much more difficult, so you effectively deny the gear to your 'competition' by awakening the sleeper.<br>
<br>
The sleeper itself can't be killed, so there's not really a direct reason to do so, it's mostly indirect stuff.  Generally a guild will awaken Kerafym (the sleeper) when they've farmed all the items they need from the warders and/or the sleeper is at risk of being awoken by a rival guild.<br>
<br>
That's my thoughts on it.<br>
